abstract: Judge Paul R. Hays, the senior member of the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, who was known for his strong views on judicial restraint, Wednesday night in Tucson, Ariz., where he was vacationing at the Lodge on the Desert. He was 76 years old and lived in Manhattan.

abstract: SANTA ANA, Calif., Feb. 5 (UPI)-- Theodore Frank, convicted last month of torturing and slaying 2-year-old Amy Sue Seitz, was formally sentenced yesterday to die in the gas chamber. Judge Byron McMillan of Superior Court denied a defense motion asking him to ignore the jury's recommendation and let the prisoner spend the rest of his life in prison without possibility of parole.
